Getting Started with txschooldata

Source: vignettes/quickstart.Rmd
quickstart.Rmd

Installation

# install.packages("remotes")
remotes::install_github("almartin82/txschooldata")

Basic Usage

library(txschooldata)
library(dplyr)

# Fetch 2024 data (2023-24 school year)
enr <- fetch_enr(2024)

Data is returned in tidy (long) format by default. Each row is one subgroup for one entity (state/district/campus).

Key Columns

Column Description
end_year School year end (2024 = 2023-24)
district_id 6-digit district ID
district_name District name
subgroup Demographic group
grade_level Grade (“TOTAL”, “K”, “01”-“12”)
n_students Student count
pct Percent of total
is_state, is_district, is_campus Level flags

Filtering by Level

# State totals
enr |>
  filter(is_state, subgroup == "total_enrollment", grade_level == "TOTAL")
##   end_year  type district_id campus_id district_name campus_name county region
## 1     2024 State        <NA>      <NA>          <NA>        <NA>   <NA>   <NA>
##   charter_flag grade_level         subgroup n_students pct aggregation_flag
## 1         <NA>       TOTAL total_enrollment    5517464   1            state
##   is_state is_district is_campus is_charter
## 1     TRUE       FALSE     FALSE      FALSE

Demographics for One District

# Austin ISD demographics
enr |>
  filter(
    district_id == "101912",
    is_district,
    grade_level == "TOTAL",
    subgroup != "total_enrollment"
  ) |>
  arrange(desc(n_students)) |>
  select(subgroup, n_students, pct)

Enrollment by Year

# 2024 enrollment
enr_2024 <- fetch_enr(2024)

# State total
enr_2024 |>
  filter(is_state, subgroup == "total_enrollment", grade_level == "TOTAL") |>
  select(end_year, n_students)
##   end_year n_students
## 1     2024    5517464

Wide Format

For one column per demographic:

enr_wide <- fetch_enr(2024, tidy = FALSE)

Visualization

library(ggplot2)
library(scales)

# 2024 enrollment (reusing from previous chunk)
enr_2024 |>
  filter(
    is_state,
    subgroup %in% c("white", "black", "hispanic", "asian"),
    grade_level == "TOTAL"
  ) |>
  ggplot(aes(x = reorder(subgroup, -pct), y = pct, fill = subgroup)) +
  geom_col() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = percent_format()) +
  labs(
    title = "Texas Public School Demographics (2024)",
    x = "Demographic Group", y = "Percent", fill = NULL
  ) +
  theme_minimal()

Available Subgroups

Demographics: white, black, hispanic, asian, native_american, pacific_islander, multiracial

Special Populations: special_ed, lep (English learners), econ_disadv

Totals: total_enrollment
